						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab lying in the Dyāmavva temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>12th-13th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th-13th Century A.D.,</hi> states that this is the <hi rend="italic">niśidhi</hi> of Siṅgiseṭṭi, Dēviseṭṭi, Padumavva and Siṅgeya who were the disciples of <hi rend="bold">Nēmidēva</hi> of the Iṅgaḷēśvara lineage belonging to Mūla-saṁgha, Dēsi-gaṇa, Koṇḍakunda anvaya and Pustaka-gachchha.</p>						

						</summary>
